how can i load photos on my ipod from another computer points please help me i loaded itunes on a computer and i can't load the photos from my laptop without removing the music and photos in it already how can i not make this happen okay what i did was made a seperate folder in my music folder titled ipod photos then i went through all my pictures copied the ones i want to be on my ipod pasted themm into my ipod photos folder then after i got all the pictures i wanted i plugged in my ipod then went to the photos tab when the itunes recognized my ipod then i checked the box where it says sync photos from the select your ipod photos folder then after you have done that click the circle next to where it says all photos that way it gets all the pictures you have in that folder then click sync at the bottom right hand corner it's that easy if you want to delete photos from your ipod simply open up your ipod photos folder delete the pictures you dont want then plug in your ipod the photos will be deleted e mail me if you have any other questions or if i was too confusing lol IPod ITunes IPod shuffle Mouse (computing) Macintosh Finder ILife FairPlay Mac OS X ITunes Music Store Windows Vista IPod nano Danger Hiptop Podcasting Apple Computer Mac OS X v10.4 PlayStation Portable File system IPod photo IPod mini Windows XP Gramophone record Windows 2000 Floppy disk Digital audio player Object Desktop USB flash drive File Allocation Table P__li Apple typography Jack plug Windows Picture and Fax Viewer IPhoto Gmail Online music store Konqueror Disc jockey Digital rights management HTTP cookie RealNetworks History of the graphical user interface Uploading and downloading Spark plug U2 (band) Computer forensics Hash table SonicStage Redundant array of independent disks E-mail spam Sudoku Mozilla Thunderbird Touchpad Computer virus Laptop IBM PC compatible Advanced Audio Coding Domestic AC power plugs and sockets Google File folder Exclamation mark Apple Newton Spatial file manager 